{"title_page": "Wrestling at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's freestyle 69 kg", "text_new": "{{Infobox Olympic event\n|event = Men's freestyle 69 kg\n|games = 2000 Summer \n|image = \n|caption =\n|venue = [[Sydney Convention and Exhibition Centre]]\n|date = 29 September \u2013 1 October\n|competitors = 20\n|nations = 20\n|gold        = [[Daniel Igali]]\n|goldNOC     = CAN\n|silver      = [[Arsen Gitinov]]\n|silverNOC   = RUS\n|bronze      = [[Lincoln McIlravy]]\n|bronzeNOC   = USA\n|prev = [[Wrestling at the 1996 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's freestyle 68 kg|1996]]\n|next = [[Wrestling at the 2004 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's freestyle 66 kg|2004]]\n}}\n{{WrestlingAt2000SummerOlympics}}\nThe '''men's freestyle 69&nbsp;kg at the [[2000 Summer Olympics]]''' as part of the [[Wrestling at the 2000 Summer Olympics|wrestling program]] was held at the [[Sydney Convention and Exhibition Centre]] from September 29 to October 1. The competition held with an elimination system of three or four wrestlers in each pool, with the winners qualify for the quarterfinals, semifinals and final by way of direct elimination.<ref name=\"SR\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/2000/WRE/mens-welterweight-freestyle.html |title=Wrestling at the 2000 Sydney Summer Games: Men's Welterweight, Freestyle |work=Sports Reference |accessdate=6 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Schedule==\n<small>All times are [[Australian Eastern Daylight Time]] ([[UTC+11:00]])</small>\n{|class = \"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! width=150|Date\n! width=50|Time\n! width=100|Event\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 29 September 2000 || 09:30 || Round 1\n|-\n| 17:00 || Round 2\n|-\n| 30 September 2000 || 09:30 || Round 3\n|-\n| rowspan=3| 1 October 2000 || 09:00 || Quarterfinals\n|-\n| 09:00 || Semifinals\n|-\n| 14:30 || bgcolor=ffffcc|Finals\n|}\n\n== Results ==\n;Legend\n*'''EF''' \u2014 Victory by forfeit, the loser is not classified\n*'''E2''' \u2014 Both wrestlers are disqualified for violation of the rules\n*'''EV''' \u2014 Disqualification from all competition for violation of the rules\n*'''EX''' \u2014 3 cautions or violation of the rules\n*'''PA''' \u2014 Injury default\n*'''PO''' \u2014 Victory by points, the loser without technical points\n*'''PP''' \u2014 Victory by points, the loser with technical points\n*'''SP''' \u2014 Technical superiority, 10 points difference, the loser with points\n*'''ST''' \u2014 Technical superiority, 10 points difference, the loser without points\n*'''TO''' \u2014 Victory by [[Pin (amateur wrestling)|fall]]\n*'''CP''' \u2014 Classification points\n*'''TP''' \u2014 Technical points\n\n=== Elimination pools ===\n\n==== Pool 1====\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size:90% \"\n!width=250|Athlete\n!width=25|{{Tooltip|Pld|Played}}\n!width=25{{!}}{{Tooltip|W|Won}}\n!width=25{{!}}{{Tooltip|L|Lost}}\n!width=25{{!}}{{Tooltip|CP|Classification points}}\n!width=25{{!}}{{Tooltip|TP|Technical points}}\n|- bgcolor=\"ccffcc\"\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Daniel Igali]]|CAN|2000 Summer}}\n|2||2||0||6||5\n|- \n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Amir Tavakkolian]]|IRI|2000 Summer}}\n|2||1||1||4||7\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Emzarios Bentinidis|Emzar Bedineishvili]]|GEO|2000 Summer}}\n|2||0||2||1||4\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size:90% \"\n! align=\"right\" width=\"250\"|\n!width=\"60\"|Score\n!align=\"left\" width=\"250\"|\n! width=\"60\" | {{Tooltip|CP|Classification points}}\n|- \n|align=\"left\"| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Emzarios Bentinidis|Emzar Bedineishvili]]|GEO|2000 Summer}} || '''4\u20135'''||align=\"left\"| '''{{flagIOCathlete|[[Amir Tavakkolian]]|IRI|2000 Summer}}'''||1\u20133 '''PP'''\n|- \n|align=\"left\"| '''{{flagIOCathlete|[[Daniel Igali]]|CAN|2000 Summer}}'''|| '''3\u20130'''||align=\"left\"| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Emzarios Bentinidis|Emzar Bedineishvili]]|GEO|2000 Summer}}||3\u20130 '''PO'''\n|- \n|align=\"left\"| {