en's Welterweight, Freestyle |work=Sports Reference |accessdate=6 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Schedule==\n<small>All times are [[Australian Eastern Daylight Time]] ([[UTC+11:00]])</small>\n{|class = \"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! width=150|Date\n! width=50|Time\n! width=100|Event\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 29 September 2000 || 09:30 || Round 1\n|-\n| 17:00 || Round 2\n|-\n| 30 September 2000 || 09:30 || Round 3\n|-\n| rowspan=3| 1 October 2000 || 09:00 || Quarterfinals\n|-\n| 09:00 || Semifinals\n|-\n| 14:30 || bgcolor=ffffcc|Finals\n|}\n\n== Results ==\n;Legend\n*'''EF''' \u2014 Victory by forfeit, the loser is not classified\n*'''E2''' \u2014 Both wrestlers are disqualified for violation of the rules\n*'''EV''' \u2014 Disqualification from all competition for violation of the rules\n*'''EX''' \u2014 3 cautions or violation of the rules\n*'''PA''' \u2014 Injury default\n*'''PO''' \u2014 Victory by points, the loser without technical points\n*'''PP''' \u2014 Victory by points, the loser with technical points\n*'''SP''' \u2014 Technical superiority, 10 points difference, the loser with points\n*'''ST''' \u2014 Technical superiority, 10 points difference, the loser without points\n*'''TO''' \u2014 Victory by [[Pin (amateur wrestling)|fall]]\n*'''CP''' \u2014 Classification points\n*'''TP''' \u2014 Technical points\n\n=== Elimination pools ===\n\n==== Pool 1====\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size:90% \"\n!width=250|Athlete\n!width=25|{{Tooltip|Pld|Played}}\n!width=25{{!}}{{Tooltip|W|Won}}\n!width=25{{!}}{{Tooltip|L|Lost}}\n!width=25{{!}}{{Tooltip|CP|Classification points}}\n!width=25{{!}}{{Tooltip|TP|Technical points}}\n|- bgcolor=\"ccffcc\"\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Daniel Igali]]|CAN|2000 Summer}}\n|2||2||0||6||5\n|- \n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Amir Tavakkolian]]|IRI|2000 Summer}}\n|2||1||1||4||7\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"| {{flagIOCathlete|[[Emzar Bedineishvili]]|GEO|2000 Summer}}\n|2||0